This doesn't model the options object case. Would a more correct version be the following?

```ts
interface Options<T> {
    context?: T;
    setup?: (this: T, script: any) => void;
    callback?: (this: T, err: string) => void;
}

declare function loader<T>(
    module: string,
    callback?: (this: T, err: string) => void,
    context?: T
): void;

declare function loader<T>(
    module: string,
    options?: Options<T>
): void;

export = loader;

```

